review:
The RPG Maker community has come up with quite some interesting games. This is one of them. Don't expect anything huge, but you'll have a unique experience with about the 1.5 hours this game takes to complete. The $2,- price tag is fair, given the limited playtime and the unique experience.

Some advice for people having trouble getting fullscreen to fill the screen. Press F1 in the game, turn off "full screen" in that menu. Then restart the game, press F5 to enter full screen and then press F6 to change the aspect to fill the screen. It worked for me.

@The creators: Please turn off this "full screen" RPG Maker option under F1 by default. This might help a lot of players.
